33namespace webrtc {
34
35class RoundRobinPacketQueue {
36 public:
37 RoundRobinPacketQueue(Timestamp start_time,
38 const WebRtcKeyValueConfig* field_trials);
39 ~RoundRobinPacketQueue();
40
41 void Push(int priority,
42 Timestamp enqueue_time,
43 uint64_t enqueue_order,
44 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet);
45 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> Pop();
46
47 bool Empty() const;
48 size_t SizeInPackets() const;
49 DataSize Size() const;
50 // If the next packet, that would be returned by Pop() if called
51 // now, is an audio packet this method returns the enqueue time
52 // of that packet. If queue is empty or top packet is not audio,
53 // returns nullopt.
54 absl::optional<Timestamp> LeadingAudioPacketEnqueueTime() const;
55
56 Timestamp OldestEnqueueTime() const;
57 TimeDelta AverageQueueTime() const;
58 void UpdateQueueTime(Timestamp now);
59 void SetPauseState(bool paused, Timestamp now);
60 void SetIncludeOverhead();
61 void SetTransportOverhead(DataSize overhead_per_packet);
62
63 private:
64 struct QueuedPacket {
65 public:
66 QueuedPacket(int priority,
67 Timestamp enqueue_time,
68 uint64_t enqueue_order,
69 std::multiset<Timestamp>::iterator enqueue_time_it,
70 std::unique_ptr<RtpPacketToSend> packet);
71 QueuedPacket(const QueuedPacket& rhs);
72 ~QueuedPacket();
73
74 bool operator<(const QueuedPacket& other) const;
75
76 int Priority() const;
77 RtpPacketMediaType Type() const;
78 uint32_t Ssrc() const;
79 Timestamp EnqueueTime() const;
80 bool IsRetransmission() const;
81 uint64_t EnqueueOrder() const;
82 RtpPacketToSend* RtpPacket() const;
83
84 std::multiset<Timestamp>::iterator EnqueueTimeIterator() const;
85 void UpdateEnqueueTimeIterator(std::multiset<Timestamp>::iterator it);
86 void SubtractPauseTime(TimeDelta pause_time_sum);
87
88 private:
89 int priority_;
90 Timestamp enqueue_time_; // Absolute time of pacer queue entry.
91 uint64_t enqueue_order_;
92 bool is_retransmission_; // Cached for performance.
93 std::multiset<Timestamp>::iterator enqueue_time_it_;
94 // Raw pointer since priority_queue doesn't allow for moving
95 // out of the container.
96 RtpPacketToSend* owned_packet_;
97 };
98
99 class PriorityPacketQueue : public std::priority_queue<QueuedPacket> {
100 public:
101 using const_iterator = container_type::const_iterator;
102 const_iterator begin() const;
103 const_iterator end() const;
104 };
105
106 struct StreamPrioKey {
107 StreamPrioKey(int priority, DataSize size)
108 : priority(priority), size(size) {}
109
110 bool operator<(const StreamPrioKey& other) const {
111 if (priority != other.priority)
112 return priority < other.priority;
113 return size < other.size;
114 }
115
116 const int priority;
117 const DataSize size;
118 };
119
120 struct Stream {
121 Stream();
122 Stream(const Stream&);
123
124 virtual ~Stream();
125
126 DataSize size;
127 uint32_t ssrc;
128
129 PriorityPacketQueue packet_queue;
130
131 // Whenever a packet is inserted for this stream we check if |priority_it|
132 // points to an element in |stream_priorities_|, and if it does it means
133 // this stream has already been scheduled, and if the scheduled priority is
134 // lower than the priority of the incoming packet we reschedule this stream
135 // with the higher priority.
136 std::multimap<StreamPrioKey, uint32_t>::iterator priority_it;
137 };
138
139 void Push(QueuedPacket packet);
140
141 DataSize PacketSize(const QueuedPacket& packet) const;
142 void MaybePromoteSinglePacketToNormalQueue();
143
144 Stream* GetHighestPriorityStream();
145
146 // Just used to verify correctness.
147 bool IsSsrcScheduled(uint32_t ssrc) const;
148
149 DataSize transport_overhead_per_packet_;
150
151 Timestamp time_last_updated_;
152
153 bool paused_;
154 size_t size_packets_;
155 DataSize size_;
156 DataSize max_size_;
157 TimeDelta queue_time_sum_;
158 TimeDelta pause_time_sum_;
159
160 // A map of streams used to prioritize from which stream to send next. We use
161 // a multimap instead of a priority_queue since the priority of a stream can
162 // change as a new packet is inserted, and a multimap allows us to remove and
163 // then reinsert a StreamPrioKey if the priority has increased.
164 std::multimap<StreamPrioKey, uint32_t> stream_priorities_;
165
166 // A map of SSRCs to Streams.
167 std::unordered_map<uint32_t, Stream> streams_;
168
169 // The enqueue time of every packet currently in the queue. Used to figure out
170 // the age of the oldest packet in the queue.
171 std::multiset<Timestamp> enqueue_times_;
172
173 absl::optional<QueuedPacket> single_packet_queue_;
174
175 bool include_overhead_;
176};
177} // namespace webrtc
178
179#endif // MODULES_PACING_ROUND_ROBIN_PACKET_QUEUE_H_
